Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Yes' radio button from 'Contrast enhanced' box from Page 03 of Pelvic MRI
And I go to Page 09 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Soft tissue mass' from the dropdown menu
And I select 'I describe' radio button

When I am on 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'Inflammatory reaction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone' checkbox is enabled
And 'Urinary bladder' checkbox is enabled
And 'Uterus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vagina' checkbox is enabled
And 'Rectum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sigma' checkbox is enabled
And 'Small intestine' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vascular' checkbox is enabled
And 'Skin/Exulceration' checkbox is enabled

And 'Strong' radio button is enabled
And 'Low' radio button is enabled
And 'No' radio button is enabled

And 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu is enabled
And '> 1 lesion, same pathology' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Inflammatory reaction' checkbox
Then the checkbox is checked
When I select 'Bone' checkbox
Then the checkbox is checked
When I select 'Urinary bladder' checkbox
Then the checkbox is checked
When I select 'Uterus' checkbox
Then the checkbox is checked
When I select 'Vagina' checkbox
Then the checkbox is checked
When I select 'Rectum' checkbox
Then the checkbox is checked
When I select 'Sigma' checkbox
Then the checkbox is checked
When I select 'Small intestine' checkbox
Then the checkbox is checked
When I select 'Vascular' checkbox
Then the checkbox is checked
When I select 'Skin/Exulceration' checkbox
Then the checkbox is checked

When I select 'Strong' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Marginal' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Homogeneous' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is selected

When I select 'Heterogeneous' radio button
Then 'Heterogeneous' radio button is selected

When I select 'Marginal' radio button
Then 'Marginal' radio button is selected


When I select 'Low' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Marginal' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Homogeneous' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is selected

When I select 'Heterogeneous' radio button
Then 'Heterogeneous' radio button is selected

When I select 'Marginal' radio button
Then 'Marginal' radio button is selected


When I select any diagnosis from 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu
Then 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select any diagnosis from 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled

When I check '> 1 lesion, same pathology' checkbox
Then the checkbox is checked
